<br>
I am quite happy gallivanting about Norrath touting my superior talents, as are my Dark Brothers and Sisters here in the Arrows.  I THINK I'm speaking for all of us, (Athame, Osgoode, Fariarya) when I say that we revel in our ability to go virtually anywhere and do anything.  We AMAZE even ourselves at our power at doing things alone.  And in a group, we bask in the glory of playing healer, rezzer, mezzer, and group buffer.  (<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Sick of me yet? hehe)  But it has a dark side... it can go too far, and we generally hate each other for it.<br>
<br>
Don't get me wrong.  Arrow Necromancers are ARROWS through and through and I'm not talking about them.  And there are exceptions to the rule but in general... NECROMANCERS ARE AWFUL!  Here's my rant:<br>
<br>
I'm duoing with a wizzy aquaintance in PoN the other day, as I have done before, and he mentions that another Necromancer friend of his is on the way.  This NEC arrives and we group and he's not friendly so neither am I and we are generally pretending that the other is not there.  [NOTE: I know you other NECs know what I'm talking about.  For those of you who don't... you know how when two Pallys group up and they are like dogs who inspect and sniff each other and chat amicably about what the other one is carrying/wearing?  Well, this is the EXACT OPPOSITE, a common necro practice where you don't want to know.]  Anyway, during battle, this necromancer keeps spaming:<br>
<br>
&quot;[target] is slowed.&quot;  He says it EVERY time.<br>
<br>
We are fighting treants and ravens, not undead, so I'm not sure what's going on behind his curtain.  So finally, both as an ice breaker and curiosity, I say &quot;Say,[his name], how is it that you are slowing?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;What do you mean?&quot; he asks.<br>
<br>
&quot;I mean, what is it you are using that slows?&quot;  <br>
<br>
&quot;Darkness.  What else would I use?&quot;<br>
<br>
Okay, so I should have just let it go right there.  He's a moron and is embarassing my class wherever he goes.  But I'm a Necromancer and I can't let it go.  Plus, I can't ignore the sarcasm.  I hate sarcasm.  Sarcasm, as a tool, is mine and mine alone to dispense.  (Okay, and Del's too <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   )<br>
<br>
&quot;Oh!&quot; I say. &quot;haha I thought you had a clickable item or something that was really 'slowing' the mob, like a chanter does.&quot;  <br>
<br>
&quot;I AM slowing them.  Darkness is a slow.&quot;<br>
<br>
I ponder.  It's a silly technicality.  But he really SHOULD be educated on this.  I would be doing him a favor.  But if I say something he's not going to get it.  And I'll look preachy.  And we're Necromancers so we'll stand here hating each other in silence.  What good will come of that?  Well, evidenly I'm a preachy, know-it-all Necromancer, because I can't help myself.  <br>
<br>
&quot;Well, when people say they want a &quot;slower&quot; in their group, they mean they want a chanter or a shammy.  Those classes 'slow' the mob.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;No,&quot; he says.  &quot;Darkness is a dot.  And it slows too.&quot;  <br>
<br>
&quot;heheh,&quot;  I say...  <br>
<br>
Did you see that?  I'm trying that tactic where I start the sentence with &quot;heheh&quot; in an effort to lighten the mood and take away from the condecending nature of what I'm about to say.  However, I have forgotten that MY &quot;heheh&quot; does not nullify the condecending nature, but AMPLIFIES the condecendingness, underlines it, puts it in bold caps and screams &quot;YOU'RE #@!<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :eek --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/eek.gif ALT=":eek"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   ing STUPID!&quot;<br>
<br>
I say, &quot;heheh, the 'slowed' message is generally done by a class that slows down the creatures attack.'<br>
<br>
&quot;That's what I'm doing.  The mob slows down.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Well, Darkness is generally referred to as a snare.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;We don't snare.&quot; he says.  <br>
<br>
This is pointless.  &quot;lol okay,&quot; I say.<br>
<br>
That's a fake &quot;lol&quot; right there.  No caps or punctuation.  I know it's fake.  He knows it.  The wizzy knows it.  It's gotten so cold in the chat box that his shrunken skelly pet has turned into a blue block of ice and hasn't moved an inch to chase the treant we're fighting.  He can't stand it.<br>
<br>
&quot;Snare is a druid spell,&quot; he says.  &quot;Darkness SLOWS the mob down and is doing damage.&quot;<br>
<br>
At this moment, with the treant dead.  The wizzy suddenly speaks up.  &quot;Guys, I have to go.&quot;  Imagine that!  Some huge emergency somewhere at this very moment!  <br>
<br>
This necro disbands faster than you can say &quot;Cazic.&quot;  I Gate out, hoping to miss any rude gestures that show up.<br>
<br>
Later that night... I go to EQRaids and check in on the Plane of Sky raid I've signed up for.  Lo and behold if this necromancer hasn't signed up and made 3 rants embarassing himself in front of the whole sign up.  Not to mention his attempt to do an end run around me and get dibs on the very epic piece I'm needing AND HAVE POSTED ABOUT ON THE SIGN IN SHEET ALREADY.<br>
<br>
I know, I know... the fact that I MADE this rant I have made my own point that Necromancers are an isolationist, anti social, ego-centered lot of bones who can't stand to let sleeping dogs lie.  But at least I am vindicated by our totally opposite attitudes in the EQRaids forums and everyone can see that, tho I AM an ego-centered moron myself, at least I'm not as bad as the next guy!  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :hat --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/pimp.gif ALT=":hat"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
I leave you with the Necromancer motto... <br>
<br>
&quot;Two Necromancers on a raid is one too many.&quot;<br>
<br>
